
1) What is a Spring Bean?
A "Spring Bean" is simply a Java object. When Java objects are created by the Spring Container, then Spring refers to them as "Spring Beans".

2) For "prototype" scoped beans, Spring does not call the destroy (or @PreDestroy) method. 

3) How can we create code to call the destroy method on prototype scope beans?

The prototype scoped beans MUST implement the DisposableBean interface. This interface defines a "destory()" method or we can use BeanPostProcessor aswell.

4) What is a real-time use caese for @Bean?

If there is a external Java file that you can not modify by adding @Component annotation, you can use @Bean annotation to include this bean to integrate it SpringFramework.

5) How to start auto-generated id values from an exact number

By processing this query:
	ALTER TABLE your_schema.your_table AUTO_INCREMENT = your_number_choice

6) How to reset auto_increment value to 1

This query will reset all rules on the table:
	truncate your_schema.your_table


7) Some query examples with defining FK

CREATE TABLE `instructor` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `first_name` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `last_name` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `email` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `instructor_detail_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  CONSTRAINT `FK_DETAIL` FOREIGN  KEY (`instructor_detail_id`) REFERENCES `instructor_detail` (`id`)
);

CREATE TABLE `instructor_detail` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `youtube_channel` varchar(128) DEFAULT NULL,
  `hobby` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=1 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;


DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `instructor`;

CREATE TABLE `instructor` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `first_name` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `last_name` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `email` varchar(45) DEFAULT NULL,
  `instructor_detail_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `FK_DETAIL_idx` (`instructor_detail_id`),
  CONSTRAINT `FK_DETAIL` FOREIGN KEY (`instructor_detail_id`) REFERENCES `instructor_detail` (`id`) ON DELETE NO ACTION ON UPDATE NO ACTION
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=1 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

